outputs.output_descr:
i. A Master's of Arts in Gender-Aware Economics,  to be hosted and delivered by the University of Bahrain, a prominent and regionally known university to benefit Bahraini citizens and the Arab region;
ii. GEPMI tailored country-level policy advisory services, to be monitored and organized by UNDP in collaboration with the University of Bahrain and GEPMI's network of international and Arab regional experts, to respond to the immediate and specific needs of Arab governments.
iii. A policy makers course on Gender-Responsive Economic Policy Management, to be hosted and delivered in Arabic by the University of Bahrain to benefit Bahraini policy makers and the Arab states region.
